Police in Jigawa State have raided a kidnappersâ€™ den and arrested two suspects who have been involving in kidnapping activities in the state. Police Spokesman in the state, ASP Lawan Shiisu Adam confirmed the arrest in a statement forwarded to DAILY POST. It was reported that bandits, armed with dangerous weapons had on December 12, 2021, stormed Bosuwa village and kidnapped a 70-year-old Alh Ali Umar and a 23-year-old Zainab Isa to unknown destination. The police spokesman said, base on intelligence report, a team of Policemen attached to Garki Divisional Police Headquarters and arrested the suspects. The suspects arrested included a 35-year-old Rabiu Audu and a 43-year-old
Alh Isah Muhammed after police raided their camp at Dandagare Village, Garki Local Government Area. He said state Commissioner of Police, A S Tafida has ordered the case to be transferred to SCID Dutse, for discreet investigation. Shiisu said the suspects will be charged to court after investigation for prosecution.